	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Glop Top Question</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />By the way the real name of this technology is &quot;Chip on board&quot;, not &quot;Glop Top&quot; and it's extremely widely used in mass-produced consummer electronics, not just NES cartridges.<br /><br />After too many units of a boards are produced, it's a waste of time and space to package all those chips when you could simply tie the chip to the board directly.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


