		<td><b>Re: Glop Top Question</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Age can make those epoxy blobs very brittle.<br /><br />I had a copy of Super Momotaro Densetu for PC Engine, and cannibalized the case to make a nice case for my TG16 Everdrive, so I thought I'd take off the protective plastic on the Hu-Card and take a look at the chips under it.<br /><br />The act of bending the hu-card caused the epoxy blobs to literally disintegrate from the chip, leaving the bare silicon and wire bonding relatively unharmed.<br /><br />It was pretty cool.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
